. ID . : hike_data %>% mutate(id = row_number()) %>% relocate(id) id , . mutate(id = row_number(), .before = name)

hike<- hike_data %>% 
  mutate(id = row_number(), .before = everything()) %>% 
  separate(col = location,
           into = c("region", "area"),
           sep = "\\s--\\s",
           fill = "right") %>% 
  separate(col = length,
           into = c("length_miles", "type"),
           sep = "\\smiles,?\\s") %>% 
  type_convert() %>% 
  mutate(rating = na_if(rating, 0))

, ? nest() / unnest unnest(cols = features) - , , features. .

hike_long<- hike %>% 
  unnest(col = features)
hike_wide<- hike %>% 
  unnest(col = features) %>% 
  mutate(value = TRUE) %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = features, 
              values_from = value,
              values_fill = FALSE) 

features_ratio_by_region <- hike_wide %>% 
  group_by(region) %>% 
  summarise(across(`Dogs allowed on leash`:Summits, mean)) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = `Dogs allowed on leash`:Summits,
               names_to = "features",
               values_to = "ratio") %>% 
  arrange(region, features)

Visualization

features_ratio_by_region %>% 
ggplot()+
  geom_bar(aes(x=region, y=ratio, fill = region), stat = "identity")+ 
  coord_flip()

limits = c(0,1) 100%, 80%,
